TITLE: Adding Custom Fields to GraphQL Types
DESCRIPTION: PHP example showing how to add a custom thumbnail field to the EntryInterface type, including width arguments and image manipulation.

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use GraphQL\Type\Definition\Type;
use Statamic\Facades\GraphQL;
use Statamic\Facades\Image;
use Statamic\Facades\URL;

GraphQL::addField('EntryInterface', 'thumbnail', function () {
    return [
        'type' => GraphQL::string(),
        'args' => [
            'width' => [
                'type' => GraphQL::int(),
            ]
        ],
        'resolve' => function ($entry, $args) {
            $asset = $entry->image;
            $url = Image::manipulate($asset)->width($args['width'])->build();
            return URL::makeAbsolute($url);
        }
    ];
});
```

