TITLE: Using isDirty and isClean Methods in Statamic
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use isDirty and isClean methods to check if an item's data has changed since it was last saved. These methods can check all attributes or specific named attributes to determine their dirty/clean state.

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
$entry->title; // "Post title"
$entry->image; // "/path/to/image.jpg"

$entry->title = 'New Title';

$entry->isDirty(); // true
$entry->isDirty('title'); // true
$entry->isDirty('image'); // false
$entry->isDirty(['image', 'title']); // true

$entry->isClean(); // false
$entry->isClean('title'); // false
$entry->isClean('image'); // true
$entry->isClean(['image', 'title']); // false

$entry->save();

$entry->isDirty(); // false
$entry->isClean(); // true
```

