TITLE: Modifying Sessions Table Schema for UUID User IDs in Laravel
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to modify the Laravel sessions table schema to accommodate Statamic's UUID user IDs. It changes the user_id column from foreignId (integer) to string type to prevent '419 Page Expired' errors when using the database session driver.

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
Schema::create('sessions', function (Blueprint $table) {
    $table->string('id')->primary();
    $table->foreignId('user_id')->nullable()->index(); // [tl! remove]
    $table->string('user_id')->nullable()->index(); // [tl! add]
    $table->string('ip_address', 45)->nullable();
    $table->text('user_agent')->nullable();
    $table->longText('payload');
    $table->integer('last_activity')->index();
});
```

