TITLE: Transforming Field Values for Search Index in PHP
DESCRIPTION: PHP configuration that transforms field values before they are stored in the search index. Includes examples of both simple transformations and complex multi-field transformations.

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
'fields' => ['title', 'address'],
'transformers' => [

    // Return a value to store in the index.
    'title' => function ($title) {
        return ucfirst($title);
    },

    // Return an array of values to be stored.
    // These will all be separate searchable fields in the index.
    // $value is the current value
    // $searchable is the object that $value has been plucked from
    'address' => function ($value, $searchable) {
        return [
            '_geoloc' => $value['geolocation'],
            'location' => $value['location'],
            'region' => $value['region'],
        ];
    }
]
```

