TITLE: Implementing Custom EntryQueryBuilder for Eloquent-Based Storage
DESCRIPTION: This EntryQueryBuilder extends Statamic's EloquentQueryBuilder to provide entry-specific functionality. It defines columns that map to the database, transforms Eloquent models into Statamic Entry objects, and handles JSON field queries.

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

namespace Statamic\Eloquent\Entries;

use Statamic\Contracts\Entries\QueryBuilder;
use Statamic\Entries\EntryCollection;
use Statamic\Query\EloquentQueryBuilder;
use Statamic\Stache\Query\QueriesTaxonomizedEntries;

class EntryQueryBuilder extends EloquentQueryBuilder implements QueryBuilder
{
    protected $columns = [
        'id', 'site', 'origin_id', 'published', 'status', 'slug', 'uri',
        'date', 'collection', 'created_at', 'updated_at',
    ];

    protected function transform($items, $columns = [])
    {
        return EntryCollection::make($items)->map(function ($model) {
            return Entry::fromModel($model);
        });
    }

    protected function column($column)
    {
        if (! in_array($column, $this->columns)) {
            $column = 'data->'.$column;
        }

        return $column;
    }
}
```

